# Real-Time Advertising Analytics: Using Dataiku to Blend Google Ads, CM360, and In-House Sales Data

### The Challenge: Data Silos and Delayed Insights

Imagine a scenario: Your marketing team is running a large-scale advertising campaign across multiple channels, including Google Ads and display ads managed through CM360. Meanwhile, your sales team is tracking leads and conversions in your CRM. The problem? These datasets live in separate environments, hindering your ability to quickly answer critical questions like:

### Dataiku: A Central Hub for Advertising Data

Dataiku offers a powerful solution for breaking down data silos and creating a unified view of your advertising performance. ### Example: SQL Transformation in Dataiku

Here's an example of how you might use SQL within Dataiku to transform and aggregate your data:

```sql
SELECT
    campaign_id,
    ad_group_id,
    date,
    SUM(impressions) AS total_impressions,
    SUM(clicks) AS total_clicks,
    SUM(cost) AS total_cost,
    SUM(conversions) AS total_conversions
FROM
    google_ads_data
GROUP BY
    campaign_id,
    ad_group_id,
    date
ORDER BY
    date DESC;
```

This SQL query aggregates Google Ads data by campaign ID, ad group ID, and date, providing a daily summary of key metrics. You can easily incorporate this query into a Dataiku recipe to perform complex data transformations.
